# Design Bible (ADR-0022)

Before adding or redesigning product UI:

1. Read `docs/design/README.md`
2. Obey UX Principles, Tokens, Typography, Accessibility, Performance Budgets
3. Complete Component Acceptance for new components
4. Complete Feature Acceptance for product features

## Hard rules

- Workflows over pages; eight primary surfaces max
- Terminal is the only live execution surface
- Real data or elegant empty states — never fabricate
- IBM Plex Sans/Mono; steel tokens; no neon/atmosphere gradients
- Motion 180–220ms; keyboard-first; OS desks zero page-scroll
- Do not casually modify `components/terminal|book|research|counsel/`

## Quality gate

`tsc` · ESLint · production build · tests · CI green. Never weaken types.

PRs must reference Design Bible compliance when touching frontend product UX.
